    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-12-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="176"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <head>176. National Security Action Memorandum No. 276<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d176fn0">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1"
                            >S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 72 <gloss
                            target="#t_D1">D</gloss> 316, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> No.
                        276. Secret. A copy was sent to the Director of the Bureau of the
                        Budget.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-12-26">December 26, 1963</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>MEMORANDUM FOR</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Administrator, Agency for International Development</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Distribution of Foreign Aid Cuts</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President will wish to review the program changes proposed in the <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1964 foreign aid program as a result of
                    Congressional action this year,<note n="1" xml:id="d176fn1">See <ref
                            target="#d175">Document 175</ref>.</note> since the way in which these
                    cuts are distributed may involve important foreign policy decisions.</p>
                <p>Therefore, <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> and the Department of Defense
                    should outline briefly the major changes proposed from the $4.5 billion <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1964 presentation figure, with a brief
                    recapitulation of the reasons for each. Any forced reductions in commitments or
                    implied commitments should also be appropriately mentioned. I suggest that
                    individual mention need be made only of changes over $10 million, e.g. a cut in
                    a country program, lumping the remainder together in appropriate categories. The
                    Department of State might submit any alternative recommendations with respect to
                    these program changes which it feels required from the foreign policy point of
                    view.</p>
                <p>I would like to be able to show these reports to the President by 7 January.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
